  "source_file": "custom_chip_PCR_prep.ot2.apiv2.py",
  "intent_precise": "Custom Chip PCR Preparation: Using tc_plate (pcr_plate, slot thermocycler plate), tubes (labware, slot 2ml Eppendorf snapcap reagent tubes), custom chip on shaker (labware, slot 1), PCR strips (labware, slot 2). With thermocycler module, temperature module. (1) Open thermocycler lid. (2) Operate thermocycler. (3) Transfer from source to destination. (4) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (5) Mix 10 times at 20\u00b5L. (6) Distribute 3\u00b5L from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 (4 wells). (7) Mix 10 times at 9\u00b5L. (8) Transfer 25\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (9) Close thermocycler lid. (10) Set temperature to 95\u00b0C. (11) Run thermocycler profile for 40 cycles. (12) Set temperature to 72\u00b0C. (13) Set temperature to 12\u00b0C. (14) Open thermocycler lid.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform distribute to A1-A1 (4 wells), temperature control (12\u00b0C, 72\u00b0C, 95\u00b0C), thermocycling. (volumes 3\u00b5L-50\u00b5L)",
  "intent": "For this Custom Chip PCR Preparation, start by opening the thermocycler lid and transferring your samples from the reagent tubes to well A1 of the PCR plate, then mix 10 times at 20\u00b5L and distribute 3\u00b5L to each of the 4 destination wells A1-A1, followed by mixing 10 times at 9\u00b5L. Next, transfer 25\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1, close the thermocycler lid, and run your PCR program starting at 95\u00b0C for 40 cycles, then step down to 72\u00b0C, and finally hold at 12\u00b0C before opening the lid. Make sure you have your custom chip positioned on the shaker in slot 1 and your PCR strips ready in slot 2 throughout the process.",
